<item>
            <title>[HBASE-3118] HBaseAdmin.createTable and modifyTable should have a family check</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-3118</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Currently HBaseAdmin.modifyTable does not check whether any family is supplied or not. I can execute this method without supplying any families and that puts the table in inconsistent state.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In my opinion, modifyTable should let you modifyTable without overwriting. But looks like it doesn&apos;t do that. This can be very dangerous as you can end up overwriting a table in production and loose data. But if we are going to keep the behavior then at least some checks should be added to make it safer.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>&lt;p&gt;0.20.6, Linux, Java 1.6+&lt;/p&gt;</environment>
