                            <comment id="12922214" author="kannanm" created="Mon, 18 Oct 2010 18:55:12 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;On a related note, if you use alter table to change the settings for a CF, you must provide all the non-default settings once again even if you don&apos;t want to change them.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;For example, if you had VERSION =&amp;gt; 5, COMPRESSION =&amp;gt; &apos;NONE&apos; on a column family, and you did an alter, and provided just COMPRESSION =&amp;gt; &apos;LZO&apos;, then the VERSION setting reverts back to the default (3).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It would be nice if the &quot;alter&quot; read the old state, and applied only the delta change.&lt;/p&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="12922234" author="streamy" created="Mon, 18 Oct 2010 20:17:08 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;@Kannan, Yeah &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-2984&quot; title=&quot;[shell] Altering a family shouldn&amp;#39;t reset to default unchanged attributes&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-2984&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-2984&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; is currently a blocker against 0.90 to do just that&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14067265" author="apurtell" created="Sat, 19 Jul 2014 00:20:05 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;We sanity check descriptors passed in for admin actions now.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
